AngloGold, Old Mutual, Sasol May Move: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-08-10T04:30:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/anglogold-old-mutual-sasol-may-move-south-african-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are from
the close of trade. Yesterday was a public holiday in South
Africa.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell for a fifth day to
its lowest close since Sept. 10, plunging 865.57, or 3 percent,
to 28,391.18.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  : Gold futures gained for a
third day after the  Federal Reserve , seeking to bolster the
economy, pledged to keep interest rates low through mid-2013,
boosting demand for the metal as a haven investment. AngloGold,
the third-largest gold miner, rose 2.4 percent to 301.89 rand.  Old Mutual Plc (OML)  : The U.K.’s third-largest insurer by
market value was downgraded to “sell” from “hold” at Standard &
Poor’s by equity analyst Tony Silverman. The shares fell 0.2
percent to 12.65 rand.  Sasol Ltd. (SOL)  : Oil rebounded from a 10-month low in
New York as investors bet fuel demand will increase amid
shrinking stockpiles and comments by the Federal Reserve that it
is prepared to use a range of tools to bolster the economy.
Sasol, the world’s biggest manufacturer of motor fuel from coal,
fell 2.4 percent to 306.83 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 